Abstract:
A school system backend manages data for students, teachers, classes, and grades, typically using
REST APIs with Node.js/Express, Python/Django, or PHP/Laravel, combined with databases like PostgreSQL or MongoDB. Key functionalities include role-based authentication
(admin, teacher, student), CRUD operations for user records, attendance tracking, and reporting.


Core Backend Components & Technology Stack:
API Development: Node.js + Express.js (TypeScript), PHP, or ASP.NET Core 8.0.
Database Management: PostgreSQL (often with Prisma ORM or TypeORM) or MongoDB (MERN stack).
Authentication: JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for secure, role-based access.
Key Entities (Schema Design):
Users: Admin, Teachers, Students, Parents.
Academic: Classes, Subjects, Lessons, Exams, Assignments.
Operational: Attendance, Timetables, Fees.


// Example: Creating a Student record using Express and Prisma
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';
import express from 'express';

const prisma = new PrismaClient();
const app = express();
app.use(express.json());

// Create a new student
app.post('/api/students', async (req, res) => {
  const { name, email, classId } = req.body;
  try {
    const student = await prisma.student.create({
      data: { name, email, classId },
    });
    res.status(201).json(student);
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(400).json({ error: "Unable to create student" });
  }
});

app.listen(3000, () => console.log('Server running on port 3000'));



Common Backend Features
CRUD Operations: Creating, reading, updating, and deleting records for teachers, students, and classes.
Attendance System: Tracking daily attendance.
Analytics: Displaying student performance graphs, teacher salary expenses, and fee collection reports.
File Management: Handling uploads for student avatars or assignment submissions (e.g., Cloudinary).
Push Notifications: Using services like Firebase for updates

